    <chapter xml:id="c-dashboard-customization-doc_purpose">
        <title>Purpose of this Document</title>
        <para>
            &PRODUCT; includes a dashboard application that educators can 
            use to examine education data from the data store. IT staff for 
            state and district school systems can customize the dashboard 
            experience to best meet the needs of their educators. 
            Customizations are expressed using 
            JavaScript Object Notation (JSON), a lightweight data exchange 
            format (see 
            <link xlink:href="http://json.org">json.org</link>). 
            This document provides a tutorial and reference for those 
            charged with implementing these customizations.
        </para>
        <para>
            Using this document as a guide, the reader should be able to:
        </para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Identify key components in a pre-defined dashboard 
                    configuration expressed in JSON.
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Write JSON to express customizations to the dashboard, 
                    using the default configuration as a starting point 
                    and reference. 
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Use the inBloom Dashboard interface to upload that 
                    custom JSON.
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>
            The content in this standalone publication may be included as
            part of other documents in future releases.
        </para>
    </chapter>
    
